Class ItemSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.kit.data.ItemSet

  • public class ItemSet
extends java.lang.Object
    Data Collection representing a collection of Item, that can calculate the total value of the items in the set.

      • filterByDateRange

        public ItemSet filterByDateRange(java.lang.String lowerDateString,
                                 java.lang.String upperDateString)
        Filters the current set of Items based on a specified date range. Items with an acquisition date within the specified range are included in the result.
        Parameters:
        lowerDateString - The lower bound of the date range in string format.
        upperDateString - The upper bound of the date range in string format.
        Returns:
        An ItemSet containing items within the specified date range.

      • filterByTags

        public ItemSet filterByTags(java.util.ArrayList<Tag> tags)
        Filters the current set of Items based on a set of tags. Only items containing all specified tags are included in the result.
        Parameters:
        tags - An ArrayList of Tag objects to filter the items by.
        Returns:
        An ItemSet containing items that match all the provided tags.

      • filterByMakes

        public ItemSet filterByMakes(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> makes)
        Filters the current set of Items based on a list of makes. Only items whose make matches one of the specified makes are included in the result.
        Parameters:
        makes - An ArrayList of strings representing the makes to filter the items by.
        Returns:
        An ItemSet containing items that match any of the provided makes.
